Package: allrelay
Version: 0.2.2
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: v4l2loopback-dkms, ffmpeg, pulseaudio-utils
Maintainer: AllRelay <allrelay@localhost>
Description: Stream Android phone media to PC over Wi-Fi
 AllRelay streams camera, screen, microphone, and speaker between
 a rooted Android phone and an Ubuntu PC over Wi-Fi, with a web-based
 dashboard for control.
 .
 Features:
  * Camera as virtual webcam (v4l2loopback /dev/video10)
  * Speaker audio (PC -> phone) with low-latency Opus
  * Web dashboard via the `allrelay open` helper command
  * Independent streams — each can be toggled separately
